      "expandable": false
    },
    {
      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:1.1",
          "pli": "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. ",
          "en": "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:1.2",
          "pli": "Atha kho sambahulā ujjhānasaññikā devatāyo abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇā kevalakappaṃ jetavanaṃ obhāsetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā vehāsaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu. ",
          "en": "Then, late at night, several glorious deities of the Disdainful Group, lighting up the entire Jeta’s Grove, went up to the Buddha, and stood in the air. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:1.3",
          "pli": "Vehāsaṃ ṭhitā kho ekā devatā bhagavato santike imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi: ",
          "en": "Standing in the air, one deity recited this verse in the Buddha’s presence: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:2.1",
          "pli": "“Aññathā santamattānaṃ, ",
          "en": "“Someone who pretends "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:2.2",
          "pli": "aññathā yo pavedaye; ",
          "en": "to be other than they really are, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:2.3",
          "pli": "Nikacca kitavasseva, ",
          "en": "is like a cheating gambler "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:2.4",
          "pli": "bhuttaṃ theyyena tassa taṃ. ",
          "en": "who enjoys what was gained by theft. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:3.1",
          "pli": "Yañhi kayirā tañhi vade, ",
          "en": "You should only say what you would do; "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:3.2",
          "pli": "yaṃ na kayirā na taṃ vade; ",
          "en": "you shouldn’t say what you wouldn’t do. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:3.3",
          "pli": "Akarontaṃ bhāsamānaṃ, ",
          "en": "The wise will recognize "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:3.4",
          "pli": "parijānanti paṇḍitā”ti. ",
          "en": "one who talks without doing.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:4.1",
          "pli": "“Na yidaṃ bhāsitamattena, ",
          "en": "“Not just by speaking, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:4.2",
          "pli": "ekantasavanena vā; ",
          "en": "nor solely by listening, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:4.3",
          "pli": "Anukkamitave sakkā, ",
          "en": "are you able to progress "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:4.4",
          "pli": "yāyaṃ paṭipadā daḷhā; ",
          "en": "on this hard path, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:4.5",
          "pli": "Yāya dhīrā pamuccanti, ",
          "en": "by which wise ones practicing absorption "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:4.6",
          "pli": "jhāyino mārabandhanā. ",
          "en": "are released from Māra’s bonds. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:5.1",
          "pli": "Na ve dhīrā pakubbanti, ",
          "en": "The wise certainly don’t act like that, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:5.2",
          "pli": "viditvā lokapariyāyaṃ; ",
          "en": "for they understand the ways of the world. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:5.3",
          "pli": "Aññāya nibbutā dhīrā, ",
          "en": "The wise are extinguished by understanding, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:5.4",
          "pli": "tiṇṇā loke visattikan”ti. ",
          "en": "they’ve crossed over clinging to the world.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:6.1",
          "pli": "Atha kho tā devatāyo pathaviyaṃ patiṭṭhahitvā bhagavato pādesu sirasā nipatitvā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ: ",
          "en": "Then those deities landed on the ground, bowed with their heads at the Buddha’s feet and said, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:6.2",
          "pli": "“accayo no, bhante, accagamā yathābālaṃ yathāmūḷhaṃ yathāakusalaṃ, yā mayaṃ bhagavantaṃ āsādetabbaṃ amaññimhā. ",
          "en": "“We have made a mistake, sir. It was foolish, stupid, and unskillful of us to imagine we could attack the Buddha! "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:6.3",
          "pli": "Tāsaṃ no, bhante, bhagavā accayaṃ accayato paṭiggaṇhātu āyatiṃ saṃvarāyā”ti. ",
          "en": "Please, sir, accept our mistake for what it is, so we will restrain ourselves in future.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:6.4",
          "pli": "Atha kho bhagavā sitaṃ pātvākāsi. ",
          "en": "At that, the Buddha smiled. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:6.5",
          "pli": "Atha kho tā devatāyo bhiyyoso mattāya ujjhāyantiyo vehāsaṃ abbhuggañchuṃ. ",
          "en": "Then those deities, becoming even more disdainful, flew up in the air. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:6.6",
          "pli": "Ekā devatā bhagavato santike imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi: ",
          "en": "One deity recited this verse in the Buddha’s presence: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:7.1",
          "pli": "“Accayaṃ desayantīnaṃ, ",
          "en": "“If you don’t give your pardon "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:7.2",
          "pli": "yo ce na paṭigaṇhati; ",
          "en": "when a mistake is confessed, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:7.3",
          "pli": "Kopantaro dosagaru, ",
          "en": "with hidden anger and heavy hate, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:7.4",
          "pli": "sa veraṃ paṭimuñcatī”ti. ",
          "en": "you’re stuck in your enmity.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:8.1",
          "pli": "“Accayo ce na vijjetha, ",
          "en": "“If no mistake is found, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:8.2",
          "pli": "nocidhāpagataṃ siyā; ",
          "en": "if no-one’s gone astray, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:8.3",
          "pli": "Verāni na ca sammeyyuṃ, ",
          "en": "and enmities are settled, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:8.4",
          "pli": "kenīdha kusalo siyā”ti. ",
          "en": "then who could have been unskillful?” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:9.1",
          "pli": "“Kassaccayā na vijjanti, ",
          "en": "“Who makes no mistakes? "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:9.2",
          "pli": "kassa natthi apāgataṃ; ",
          "en": "Who doesn’t go astray? "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:9.3",
          "pli": "Ko na sammohamāpādi, ",
          "en": "Who doesn’t fall into confusion? "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:9.4",
          "pli": "ko ca dhīro sadā sato”ti. ",
          "en": "Who is the wise one that’s ever mindful?” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:10.1",
          "pli": "“Tathāgatassa buddhassa, ",
          "en": "“The Realized One, the Buddha, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:10.2",
          "pli": "sabbabhūtānukampino; ",
          "en": "compassionate for all beings: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:10.3",
          "pli": "Tassaccayā na vijjanti, ",
          "en": "that’s who makes no mistakes, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:10.4",
          "pli": "tassa natthi apāgataṃ; ",
          "en": "and that’s who doesn’t go astray. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:10.5",
          "pli": "So na sammohamāpādi, ",
          "en": "He doesn’t fall into confusion, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:10.6",
          "pli": "sova dhīro sadā satoti. ",
          "en": "for he’s the wise one, ever mindful. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:11.1",
          "pli": "Accayaṃ desayantīnaṃ, ",
          "en": "If you don’t give your pardon "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:11.2",
          "pli": "yo ce na paṭigaṇhati; ",
          "en": "when a mistake is confessed, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:11.3",
          "pli": "Kopantaro dosagaru, ",
          "en": "with hidden anger and heavy hate, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:11.4",
          "pli": "sa veraṃ paṭimuñcati; ",
          "en": "you’re stuck in your enmity. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:11.5",
          "pli": "Taṃ veraṃ nābhinandāmi, ",
          "en": "I don’t approve of such enmity, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn1.35:11.6",
          "pli": "paṭiggaṇhāmi voccayan”ti. ",
          "en": "and so I pardon your mistake.”"
        }
      ],
